public static @Nullable Picture makeFromData​(Data data)
        Recreates Picture that was serialized into data. Returns constructed Picture if successful; otherwise, returns null. Fails if data does not permit constructing valid Picture.

      • playback

        public Picture playback​(Canvas canvas)

        Replays the drawing commands on the specified canvas. In the case that the commands are recorded, each command in the Picture is sent separately to canvas.

        To add a single command to draw Picture to recording canvas, call Canvas.drawPicture(io.github.humbleui.skija.Picture) instead.

        Parameters:
        canvas - receiver of drawing commands
        Returns:
        this
        See Also:
        https://fiddle.skia.org/c/@Picture_playback

      • getCullRect

        public io.github.humbleui.types.Rect getCullRect()

        Returns cull Rect for this picture, passed in when Picture was created. Returned Rect does not specify clipping Rect for Picture; cull is hint of Picture bounds.

        Picture is free to discard recorded drawing commands that fall outside cull.

        Returns:
        bounds passed when Picture was created
        See Also:
        https://fiddle.skia.org/c/@Picture_cullRect

      • makePlaceholder

        public static Picture makePlaceholder​(@NotNull
                                      @NotNull io.github.humbleui.types.Rect cull)

        Returns a placeholder Picture. Result does not draw, and contains only cull Rect, a hint of its bounds. Result is immutable; it cannot be changed later. Result identifier is unique.

        Returned placeholder can be intercepted during playback to insert other commands into Canvas draw stream.

        Parameters:
        cull - placeholder dimensions
        Returns:
        placeholder with unique identifier
        See Also:
        https://fiddle.skia.org/c/@Picture_MakePlaceholder

      • getApproximateOpCount

        public int getApproximateOpCount()
        Returns the approximate number of operations in SkPicture. Returned value may be greater or less than the number of SkCanvas calls recorded: some calls may be recorded as more than one operation, other calls may be optimized away.
        Returns:
        approximate operation count
        See Also:
        https://fiddle.skia.org/c/@Picture_approximateOpCount

      • getApproximateBytesUsed

        public long getApproximateBytesUsed()
        Returns the approximate byte size of Picture. Does not include large objects referenced by Picture.
        Returns:
        approximate size
        See Also:
        https://fiddle.skia.org/c/@Picture_approximateBytesUsed

      • makeShader

        @NotNull
public @NotNull Shader makeShader​(@NotNull
                                  @NotNull FilterTileMode tmx,
                                  @NotNull
                                  @NotNull FilterTileMode tmy,
                                  @NotNull
                                  @NotNull FilterMode mode,
                                  @Nullable
                                  @Nullable Matrix33 localMatrix,
                                  @Nullable
                                  @Nullable io.github.humbleui.types.Rect tileRect)
        Return a new shader that will draw with this picture.
        Parameters:
        tmx - The tiling mode to use when sampling in the x-direction.
        tmy - The tiling mode to use when sampling in the y-direction.
        mode - How to filter the tiles
        localMatrix - Optional matrix used when sampling
        tileRect - The tile rectangle in picture coordinates: this represents the subset (or superset) of the picture used when building a tile. It is not affected by localMatrix and does not imply scaling (only translation and cropping). If null, the tile rect is considered equal to the picture bounds.
        Returns:
        Returns a new shader object. Note: this function never returns null.
